I have lived in the United States for 22 years now and the experience here has been the closest thing to back home I’ve ever experienced. The pierogi remind me of Babcia’s kitchen back home, the ambiance is like sitting in Krakow square on a sunny day, and the golompki taste just like my mom’s! I’m appreciative of this place not just for the food but also keeping my culture and memories alive! I recommend this place to anyone looking to try some amazing Polish food! They definitely get it right!

Wonderful place. The food is well made and very authentic. They definitely don't cut any corners.  I particularly love their healthy options, such as their bone broth soups, and their fresh fruit/veggie smoothies and juices. The atmosphere is very pleasant, making it a great place to just sit and read something, or browse the web on my tablet with their free Wi-Fi.

A truly delightful & understated local gem. We have a vibrant, but quiet, Polish community here in Westfield and it is a privilege to enjoy some of their amazing cuisine. I personally love sampling various pierogies but there are many other dishes to explore as well. Check for specials.
